question: [🤖 Internet of Things Robotics with Blynk and TinkerKit 🤖]
answer: Join us for an immersive workshop on the exciting intersection of IoT and robotics, utilizing Blynk and TinkerKit. This hands-on session is designed to empower you with practical skills and knowledge in the field of IoT robotics. Led by Ir. Ts. Dr. Fauzan Khairi Che Harun, Advisor of Google Developers Student Clubs UTM, this workshop will provide you with a deep dive into IoT-enabled robotics, offering insights into real-world applications and innovations. Register here: https://forms.gle/Zh8nRvSTj6S26xBV9

What are the dress code requirements for the final exams at UTM?
answer: According to the FKE Final Examination Briefing to all invigilators, you are strongly advised to follow the UTM dress code for all your final exam papers to ensure that you do not face any problem entering the exam hall. Other than the attire, you shall have: 1. No ear piercing/ear rings for boys, 2. To wear proper shoes unless the hall requires you to take off shoes, 3. No dyed hair, 4. Make sure your hair is neat.
